Package: timechange
Title: Efficient Updating of Date-Times
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: person("Vitalie", "Spinu", email = "spinuvit@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A collection of fast routines for manipulation of date-time
   objects while correctly accounting for time-zones and daylight saving
   times. Provided utilities include updating of date-time components (year,
   month, day etc.), time-zone changes, rounding and period arithmetic. Parts of
   the 'CCTZ' source code, released under the Apache 2.0 License, are included
   in this package. See <https://github.com/google/cctz> for more details.
Depends: R (>= 3.4)
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
  Rcpp (>= 0.12)
LinkingTo:
  Rcpp
Suggests:
  testthat,
  knitr,
  lubridate
LazyData: true
SystemRequirements: A system with zoneinfo data (e.g. /usr/share/zoneinfo) as
    well as a recent-enough C++11 compiler (such as g++-4.8 or later). On
    Windows the zoneinfo included with R is used.
BugReports: https://github.com/vspinu/timechange/issues
URL: https://github.com/timechange/mlvocab/
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
